'''Psychophysics Toolbox Version 3''' (PTB-3) is a collection of free functions for [[MATLAB]] or [[GNU Octave]] intended for use by neuroscience and vision researchers.<ref>{{cite web |title=Psychtoolbox-3 |date=4 January 2017 |url=http://psychtoolbox.org/ }}</ref> It synthesizes and shows accurately controlled visual and auditory stimuli and interacts with the observer. It has {{citation needed span|date=April 2017|text=at least twelve thousand active users,}} an active forum,<ref>{{cite web |title=Psychtoolbox Forum |date=4 January 2017 |website=Psychtoolbox-3 |url=http://psychtoolbox.org/forum/ }}</ref> and many citations.<ref>{{cite web |title=Citations |date=4 January 2017 |website=Psychtoolbox-3 |url=http://psychtoolbox.org/citations/ }}</ref> PTB-3 is based on the Psychophysics Toolbox Version 2 (PTB-2) but its MATLAB extensions (in C) were rewritten to be more modular and use OpenGL. Psychtoolbox is offered alongside many alternative toolboxes for programming Psychophysics and Psychology experiments, such as [[PsychJava]] for Java, or [[PsychoPy]] for Python.{{Citation needed|date=April 2017}}

Psychophysics Toolbox Version 3 is [[free software]]. Most of it is released under the [[MIT License]], but parts of it are licensed under other open source and free software licenses.<ref>{{cite web |date=5 January 2012 |title=Psychtoolbox-3/README |website=GitHub |url=https://github.com/Psychtoolbox-3/Psychtoolbox-3/blob/master/README }}</ref>

